author: Written by: Chris Franklin, Meteorologist
title: Chris: More sunshine for Monday, temps a bit warmer
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Cloudy skies on Sunday kept temperatures in the 60s with an afternoon high at Kenner at 66Â°!
We should see more sunshine for Monday and through the remainder of the week. High temperatures today should run about 10 degrees warmer. Highs will return to the low and mid 80s this week as an upper ridge builds in.
By the weekend, a weak upper trough will send a cold front into the area. This should drop temperatures into the low 80s and low humidity is expected as well.
